ion a year on our school budget yet we rate almost last in the state for ratings, even Camden which makes the Bronx look like paradise scored much higher on less money,   for $40 Million, I expect a few Nobel Prize winners,   If you are middle or working class and both parents have to work at least you have an excuse, you are just too busy making ends meet to spend quality time with your kids. One easy fix is remove all TV's, Xbox, and violent video games from your house.   Read books !! set an example, also stop feeding them garbage food, MacDonald's etc Ground them for months for cursing at an adult, missing curfew etc. I admit when I was young things were too strict but that's no reason to abdicate your responsibility as a parent, your kids are NOT your friends, they need to be trained by you !! not MTV or some splatter game. The Rich have no excuse, their little brats are spoiled rotten, well fed and basically just need a boot in the **** to straighten them out, look at Dubya, I rest my case. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1319" language="en" documentId="3141" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Neo Conjob" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:40PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="3141" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1319"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>